CHILE DAYBOOK: Central Bank President Addresses Latin Conference

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-04-15T03:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/chile-daybook-central-bank-president-addresses-latin-conference.html
Central bank President Jose De Gregorio speaks at a Latin American conference in  Washington 
hosted by the Brookings Institute at 11:30 a.m. New York time.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Finance Minister Felipe Larrain speaks to reporters on tax
collection efforts this year at 9:30 a.m. New York time.
*Cap SA, the country’s biggest steelmaker, holds a shareholder
meeting in Santiago at 10 a.m. New York time.
*Energy and Mining Minister Laurence Golborne participates in a
ceremony for the opening of the expanded Mina Carmen de
Andacollo copper mine in Coquimbo region.  EQUITIES:
*The Ipsa index rose 0.2 percent to 4,656.13.
*Cencosud SA gained 2.3 percent to 3,466.8 pesos, the steepest
increase in two weeks.  Chile ’s largest retailer by sales was
reiterated at “outperform” by Credit Suisse Group AG.  MARKETS:
*Chile’s peso weakened for the third time in four days as higher
 oil prices  and lower copper signaled a reduction in the
country’s trade surplus. The currency fell 0.1 percent to 472.80
per  U.S. dollar  as of 11:50 a.m. New York time.
*Foreign investors reduced bets against the peso in the forwards
market to $1.5 billion on April 12, the lowest in a month,
according to central bank data that shows Chilean banks’ dollar
positions with foreign counterparties.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
